page.title: 08FARM AND WOODLAND NEAR M2
page.content: {Farming Upper Nashenden Farm,owned by the Government has tenanted land and at the top of Hill Road,fields are owned by Blue Circle Cement Company which grow wheat.Rochester Mathematics School is said to own fields for wheat.Surrounding fields near to Ringshill Place belong to Mr.Gore,a farmer. {Old House First Sir Derek and Lady Watson lived at Ringshill Place,built in 1865,then Commander Cameran,now Mr.Gore.This large house with two living rooms and a dining room is not on main drainage. Many chandaliers hang from the ceilings with many plaster faces. {Common Land All that is left of Wouldham Common is a small clearing near some stables in the middle of woods.
